sentences: Known for his work as a bandleader and during the 1950s with Miles Davis, Garland helped popularize the block chord style of piano playing.
William "Red" Garland was born in 1923 in Dallas, Texas.
He began his musical studies on the clarinet and alto saxophone but, in 1941, switched to the piano.
Less than five years later, Garland joined the trumpet player Hot Lips Page, well-known in the southwest, playing with him until a tour ended in New York in March 1946.
Garland also had a short-lived career as a welterweight boxer in the 1940s.
